  "texts": [
    "Attacker Case Generation.",
    "We examine two categories of attacks: (1) direct harm attacks, which use a specific tool T a to directly damage the user, and (2) data stealing attacks, which involve using a tool T a to access and extract the user's private data, subsequently dispatching this data to the attacker via an email-sending tool, such as GmailSendEmail.",
    "When generating each attacker case, we start by randomly sampling nine tools.",
    "We then instruct GPT-4 to either select one tool capable of executing direct harm to the user or choose a tool for retrieving the user's private data.",
    "Subsequently, we ask GPT-4 to generate the attacker instruction I a using the selected tool."
  ],
